The paper discusses the interdisciplinary nature of computer science and how it has evolved over the last 50 years. It analyzes the impact of interdisciplinary research on individual fields and studies the reciprocity among fields through citation interactions. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). These sub-categories are relevant as they deal with topics related to interdisciplinary research, impact analysis, and citation interactions.
